{"chapter": 8, "question_id": 44, "text": "The provided text describes Vibha's attire in Jessore, but it does not contain any information regarding her presentation when she seeks out Ramchandra Ray in Chandradwip.\n\nIn Jessore, Vibha's appearance was dictated by the Mahishi, who ignored Vibha's preference for a simpler look. Instead of the three thin, turquoise-colored bangles Vibha desired, the Mahishi forced her to wear eight thick gold bangles and a huge diamond bracelet on each arm. Despite Vibha's feeling that a nose ring would not suit her, the Mahishi made her wear a large one. Additionally, the Mahishi insisted on a specific hairstyle after discovering that Vibha had secretly tried to have it redone to her own liking. This left Vibha feeling flustered and burdened by the weight of her jewelry and coiffure."}
